  "texts": [
    "These seven hypopigmented dermatoses were identified as pityriasis alba, pityriasis versicolor, marshall white syndrome, anemic nevus, idiopathic guttate hypomelanosis, amelanotic nevus, and hypomelanosis of Ito.",
    "Considering that the primary objective of this study was to distinguish vitiligo through dermoscopic images, which constitutes a dichotomous problem, the other seven pigmented dermatoses were collectively grouped.",
    "To enhance the assessment of the model, the dataset was divided into training and test sets in a 7:3 ratio.",
    "Within the training dataset, there are 1875 images depicting cases of vitiligo and 1150 images of non-vitiligo cases.",
    "As for the test dataset, it comprises 803 images representing vitiligo cases and 492 images non-vitiligo cases."
  ],
